Commentary Text: Watson to Karthik, out Lbw!! Karthik has been given OUT LBW. He talks with Russell and reviews it. Was it slipping down the leg-side? Don't think there's any bat on that, struck DK in front of leg-stump, but he's so back that the ball didn't have far to travel. Umpire's call on Hawk-Eye and Karthik is OUT. A handy knock from Karthik comes to an end, lovely yorker from Watson, followed Karthik slightly and struck him bang in front of leg-stump, it was the back-pad as well. The impact was in front of leg and would have been clipping the stumps. Karthik lbw b Watson 26(25) [4s-2 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Watson to Uthappa, out Uthappa Run Out!! KKR have gifted away a wicket here. Bad communication between two senior members. Length ball around off and Uthappa punched it towards cover from the crease. Raina stopped it with a dive with his left hand, picks the ball and hits the bullseye at the bowler's end. Uthappa was ball-watching and Karthik was halfway down. One had to go at the danger's end, and Uthappa went for it. This is a big wicket. Raina has his arms aloft. Uthappa run out (Raina) 29(16) [4s-2 6s-3]

Commentary Text: Watson to Nitish Rana, out Caught by Dhoni!! Dhoni pouches, up goes the umpire's finger and there's the roar from the Chepauk crowd. A soft dismissal. Commentary Text: Chawla to Dhoni, out Caught by Karthik!! Dhoni walks. Pin drop silence at Chepauk. Is that the match? Well, there is still Bravo - last game's match-winner. Dhoni waits as the umpire checks for a front foot no-ball, Chawla is fine and Dhoni continues walking. Clever bowling from Chawla, slowed it up a touch and kept it outside off, Dhoni was down on his knee to play the sweep, through the shot early and the under edge is found. Karthik has a juggle before completing the catch. Dhoni didn't even wait for the umpire. Started walking as soon as he saw the catch taken. Dhoni c Karthik b Chawla 25(28) [4s-1 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Tom Curran to Watson, out Caught by Rinku Singh!! Maiden wicket for Tom Curran in IPL. A breather for KKR there. Short of a length delivery around off and Watson pulls it hard again. But there's a fielder in the deep, it's Rinku Singh out there. He moves to his left and grabs it eventually to bring an end to Watson's blitzkrieg. CSK couldn't have asked for a better start from the Aussie all-rounder. Wait on.. the crowd at Chepauk welcomes Raina with a loud cheer. The highest run scorer for CSK in history of IPL is at the crease. Watson c Rinku Singh b Tom Curran 42(19) [4s-3 6s-3]
